result.name: Cha Cha Room

reviews.text: Very good dim sum at excellent prices. Great service. A favourite when staying at East Hotel, Hong Kong.

Not cheap at all, very pricey when consider the quality and level of service (extremely poor service, need some basic training)

Food
Dim Sum is generally poor, salty, full of MSG (that might be sth else, but which is what I feel like), not fresh at all...

Never a place to taste the real dim sum...

Hygiene 
Though the restaurant look nice, but that is not clean at all

Service
A typical mainland China service.. those you will get in most local Chinese restaurants, as if they were never train with basic. Many of them are actually immigrant from China, they might not experience the level of service expected from locals, but that is never their fault, Maxim group should providing the training required (I dont want to blame in from where they are, though their experience and culture would affect their service provided, as that is the norm for them)

1.  You don't hand out dishes above your customer's head... nor collect dirty plates over your customer, as there's risk you spill in all over your customer (This is basic!!)

2.  You should never take away one's food without asking if they are done, when there's still plenty of them left.

3. You should never expect or even order your customer to reshuffle the plate for you to serve. As a server, you should reshuffle it, before serving any dishes, again It's f****** basic!!!! 

This has been basic requirement, till last 10-15 years, server switch from locals, to immigrants from China, not sure if that is the culture in China, but that is not right. Someone should teach them the right and safe way...

 4. Never mop the floor when someone is still eating. Do that when you are closed!!!! Like 4 people mopping the whole store when you still have 10 tables of client at 4pm. 

if 4pm is late, set a last order time and close your shop, don't let you customer order and mop while they are eating....
Reasonable price for simple and quick dining. Good mushroom soup. Unfortunately the sauce on the 2 dishes (tofu and kale) is too thick and sweet.
Price reasonable and food is good.
Encountered an ill-mannered waitress in off-peak hours who left customers unattended and made extremely rude remarks. Food is alright.

result.name: 茶茶居

reviews.text: Ok啦😄⚘

性價比超低嘅點心
$28 2粒 蝦蛟，但蝦無蝦味，皮厚而且包唔實隻蝦
有肉類嘅黠心仲恐怖，超鹹.... 明顯係唔新鮮

服務唔洗講因為係無服務可言，或者可以話係中國式服務(唔係果種近年極端到會跪但好awkward果種...係傳統無禮貌唔識服務業點做果種)... 全部態度都好差...特別係做得耐D 果堆...加埋收銀 
而你食緊野會有幾個人拖地... 收野時有汁都會由你頭上過... 隨時一身都係

最後，唔好再信果個Openxxxx, 你會發現某d連鎖餐廳排名會出奇地高...
有某d連鎖嘅普通餅鋪都好高排名
人手吾夠，冇時間清理枱面導致人客久等，一片混亂，食物吾熱。

素食者地獄 跟餐有湯浸芥蘭和菜芯 要求以水焯熟蔬菜不果 只可用湯 素食者勿進
It’s the disaster of vegetarian, restaurant insisted that their vegetable could only be boiled by animal soup, I asked to boil the vegetable by water with no success, if u r a pure vegetarian MUST NOT go to this restaurant
ベジタリアンという絶対に入らないでください
セットである骨湯で作った地元の野菜が 
お湯で野菜を作った欲しくて店員から断って貰った
サービスが悪くて改善することが必要だ
西方思維，中式食品。不倫不類的茶居。繞場一周。大多數是80後的。破傳統式的營運。粉麵類。其分量只及傳統式的半份。點心類每籠只有兩件。以三，五知己而言。每款點心點二至三籠。餐桌尺度侧相形見絀。每款，每籠點心數目由顧客決定是不是會好些。食品的用料及製作算是不錯。個人認為路過此地。不進去不是損失。光顧亦無妨。
